Content.Text:
y = zeros (M);
    arg M is an integer. y is an M x M matrix of zeros
y = zeros (M, N);
    args M and N are integers. y is an M x N matrix of zeros

y = ones (M);
    arg M is an integer. y is an M x M matrix of ones
y = ones (M, N);
    args M and N are integers. y is an M x N matrix of ones

for a vector input, maximum and its index returned
    w  = [1 8 2 4 2 9 1];
    a  = max (w);
    [z, x] = max (w);

    [z, x] = max (a, b); % where a, b are scalars is also supported

for a matrix, a row vector is returned withe the max of each column

for a vector input, minimum and its index returned
    w  = [1 8 2 4 2 9 1];
    a  = min (w);
    [z, x] = min (w);

    [z, x] = min (a, b); % where a, b are scalars is also supported

for a matrix, a row vector is returned withe the min of each column
